# OpenMate extension — non-secret development defaults (FR-010 / spec 006-m1-b-deploy T035)
#
# This file is a COMMENTS-ONLY pointer. It contains no assignments and no
# secrets. Copy to `.env` and fill values locally; `.env` MUST remain
# gitignored. Never commit a real key, PEM block, webhook token, or
# admin password to this repository (FR-007).
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Committed public MCP URL (dev default, as of 2026-04-22)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   https://mcp-16-58-144-221.nip.io/
#
# Transport: MCP Streamable HTTP.
#   - Main endpoint:   POST /           (JSON-RPC envelope; responses may be
#                                        Server-Sent Events with `event: message`
#                                        and `data:` lines).
#   - Health endpoint: GET  /healthz    (unauthenticated; returns {"status":"ok"}).
#   - There is NO REST `GET /tools/list` URL; tools are listed via the MCP
#     `tools/list` JSON-RPC method on `POST /`.
#
# Session handling: the server is stateful — the first `initialize` call
# returns an `mcp-session-id` response header; subsequent JSON-RPC calls
# MUST include that value as an `mcp-session-id` request header.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Authoritative source for the live URL
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The live URL is published in the OpenMate monorepo at:
#   dophlin/openmate-mono :: DECISIONS.md :: §"Current Milestone"
#   (006-m1-b-deploy row -> "Literal live URL")
#
# If the URL in DECISIONS.md disagrees with the value above, DECISIONS.md
# WINS. That file is the single source of truth; this comment is a cached
# convenience pointer. When the owned-domain cut-over runs post-M1
# (specs/006-m1-b-deploy/infrastructure/owned-domain-cutover.md), update
# DECISIONS.md first, then this file.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API key shape (off-box consumers)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENMATE_API_KEY must match the 005 Q3=A shape:
#   sk-om-<48 chars from [0-9A-Za-z]>   (54 chars total)
#
# Placeholder only — never paste a real key here:
#   OPENMATE_API_KEY=sk-om-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
#
# The real key is distributed via the maintainer password manager. Generate
# a new key with:
#   node -e "process.stdout.write('sk-om-' + require('crypto').randomBytes(48).toString('base64').replace(/[^0-9A-Za-z]/g,'').slice(0,48) + '\n')"
#
# Rotation policy: see
#   dophlin/openmate-mono :: specs/006-m1-b-deploy/infrastructure/api-key-rotation.md
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
